    "3. Write a Python Program to Convert Decimal to Binary, Octal and Hexadecimal?\n",
    "\n",
    "Solution:-\n",
    "\n",
    "def conversion():\n",
    "    '''This function returns binary , octal and hexadecimal values of input number'''\n",
    "    num = int(input('enter a number: '))\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        print(num,'in binary is:',bin(num))\n",
    "        print(num,'in octal is:',oct(num))\n",
    "        print(num,'in hexadecimal is:',hex(num))\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(e)\n",
    "        \n",
    "----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "Output:\n",
    "conversion()\n",
    "enter a number: 344\n",
    "344 in binary is: 0b101011000\n",
    "344 in octal is: 0o530\n",
    "344 in hexadecimal is: 0x158"
